comment: Blair (WAS) jumps up for the rebound and Dellavedova (CLE) takes out his legs from underneath him.
Perkins (CLE) takes 3 steps after catching the pass.
Marion (CLE) cleanly strips the ball from Seraphin (WAS).
Seraphin (WAS) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Dellavedova's (CLE) drive to the basket and cleanly blocks his shot attempt.
Blair (WAS) braces for the contact and sets the screen on Marion (CLE) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Perkins (CLE) sets the screen on Sessions (WAS) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Dellavedova (CLE) maintains legal guarding position as Sessions (WAS) loses the ball on his drive to the basket.
Butler (WAS) moves his pivot foot at the start of his drive.
Marion (CLE) makes contact with Butler's (WAS) head that affects his layup attempt.
Perkins (CLE) moves his pivot foot.
Perkins (CLE) makes contact with Seraphin that affects his RSBQ on the drive to the basket.
Blair (WAS) sets the screen on Harris (CLE) and gives him the opportunity to stop and/or change direction.
Marion (CLE) intentionally kicks the ball on the play.
Dellavedova (CLE) reaches in and makes body to body contact with Bynum (WAS) that knocks him to the ground.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials determined that the foul committed by Dellavedova (CLE) did not meet the criteria for a Flagrant Foul.
Haywood (CLE) cleanly blocks Bynum's (WAS) layup attempt from behind.
Blair (WAS) makes contact with Haywood's (CLE) arm and the contact affects his movement to the basket and shot attempt.
Webster (WAS) inbounds the ball in less than 5 seconds.
Bynum (WAS) commits a take foul on Dellavedova (CLE).

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that the field goal attempt by Butler (WAS) was released before the game clock expired was overturned and the basket was disallowed.
